I use a big deep socket to push on the end of the push rod tube.  I  
don't remember what size, but it must fit the end of the tube in such  
a way as to push on it.  Make sure to lubricate the new seals.  You  
should both see and feel the tubes stop sliding once they've seated.

Good luck!
Zack

